<br>
  I set up groups just about the same way everytime.  Me, Cleric, Katia, 3 other melees.  Every now and then I will throw in a druid or shaman for backup healing/evac/slowing etc, if we are headed somewhere a little more difficult than usual.  (Chardok, Royal Palace comes to mind).  However, generally, I like to have trains sitting around the group, and, I want a lot of dps (Damage Per Second) to get rid of them faster.<br>
<br>
  Well, Rangers are useful for more than just dps.  Snare is nice, obviously.  Root snaring gets old after a while =P.  Their regens are nice if you don't have a shaman/druid.  Their attack buffs aren't going to make or break a group, but, they never hurt either.  And when the shit hits the fan, and the cleric is oom and I've got 10 mobs stacked up, and no mana to slow, their epic is a godsend....   <br>
<br>
  Just a few nights ago I was grouped with Kinian&lt;Landslide&gt;, and about 3-4 other melee's in Chardok.  We had no healer, and we were camped in the Observer room.  We took down the Ancient Guardian a few times (Ph for the Bridge Keeper), and the Watch Captain and Observer whatever his name is.  Fear kiting+regens+mini heals kept it going and we didn't have one death....<br>
<br>
  And yes, as others have pointed out, it takes an intuitive thinker to be a 'great ranger.'  Kinian comes to mind when I think of a great ranger... he's pretty much got a spot in my group at anytime.  He's the only ranger I have played with that snared/taunted mobs off of me when I had 6-7 beating on me without breaking a mez, and acted like that was an everyday thing that all rangers should do when I told him I was surprised to see him doing it.  And in fact, he's saved my group more than once when I had 15+ mobs sitting around because I was foolish enough to dare Katia to pull another train when I was 20 mana or so =P.  Snare gave me the extra 3-5 seconds I need to kite a mob to the other side of the room and med real fast for a mez...  or wait for ToT to reload =).   <br>
<br>
  In essence, I feel rangers are very effective in subtle ways.  They aren't considered an  'essential' class to have in your group, but, having a good one can keep you alive in situations where having an extra warrior/rogue/monk instead, won't.<br>
<br>
That's just my two cents.<br>
/cheer Rangers<br>
  <br>
Mezmith&lt;VV&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulleauaric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lleauaric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/3/02 3:38:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=772.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.att.net/~ashleyellinor/images/photoindex/deniroguns.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards, bah, let's talk about *rangers*...</span><hr size=1> True Story.<br>
<br>
When EW first were getting sleepers keys..  This is back in the old days when very few had full Kael and Vulak was only seen by wandering GMs.   <br>
EW had scrapped together about 11 keys,  these going to EWs senior group.  <br>
<br>
Well..  with 11, without all the gadgets and doohickeys we have now..  these people entered ST and proceeded to get their ass kicked..  but they kept coming back and learning from every defeat.  Getting more keys as they went along..  but on this day they only had 11<br>
<br>
They fight their way to the Final Arbitor (I think, could have been the Prog or the other one)  who had kick the shit out of them several times before.  <br>
They attack.<br>
Boom.. Sith Goes Down<br>
Boom..  Narogo goes down<br>
Boom.. A Cleric goes down<br>
<br>
All seems lost again, people are calling for the one remaining cleric to camp... until<br>
<br>
Over guildchat (im in seb listening to this) Aeno says:<br>
&quot;Im going to Tank it&quot;..  &quot;Dont Camp&quot;<br>
now a ranger saying this didnt fill me with the greatest of hope for the cause.. But I was proven wrong<br>
Aeno got aggro..and clicked on Weaponshield..  he was able to tank for even a short time after that..<br>
Giving valuble time for Sithgear and Narogo to be rezzed back in and the fight was won..  giving EW its first primal weapon I believe.<br>
<br>
So dont say Rangers are useless...  they could very well save your raid one day<br>
